The atmosphere is vibrant, with career counselors providing tips on maintaining eye contact and navigating suitable industries. A mix of companies, including a robotics startup showcasing a small drone, a cybersecurity firm conducting a password-cracking challenge, and consulting firms with glossy case study booklets, occupy colorful booths. Students analyze recruiters' enthusiasm while carrying tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, and water bottles. Workshops on networking etiquette are held in an adjoining classroom, and an alumni panel discusses technical interview preparation. Monitors near the exit display a link to a post-event survey, and university media crews capture interviews throughout the event.

The lively atmosphere, enhanced by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks, features numerous booths showcasing a diverse array of technology firms, including a robotics startup demonstrating a small flying drone and a cybersecurity company conducting a password-cracking challenge. Students engage with enthusiastic recruiters and consult career counselors offering guidance on maintaining eye contact and sending personalized follow-up emails. Workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel for interview preparation occur in an adjoining classroom. Media crews capture interviews throughout the event, while monitors display a post-event survey link near the exit.

Inside, dozens of booths with colorful banners showcase a diverse array of technology firms, including a robotics startup featuring a small flying drone and a cybersecurity company conducting a password-cracking challenge. Career counselors guide students on maintaining eye contact and navigating industries, while an alumni panel shares insights for technical interviews. Workshops on networking etiquette take place in an adjoining classroom. Students analyze enthusiastic recruiters, compare swag items such as tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens, and some international students queue outside for advice on visa sponsorship. Monitors flash a post-event survey link near the exit, and camera crews capture interviews throughout the busy event.

Alumni volunteers also offer motivational talks, with workshops on networking etiquette occurring in an adjoining classroom.

Friends relax in the quad, discussing company responses and comparing swag items.

Career counselors assist students with professional interactions, offering workshops on networking etiquette and a panel discussing interview preparation in an adjoining classroom. Volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures, while media crews capture the event's lively atmosphere.
